   "body" : "The JSON-RPC verifymessage intentionally required the user to provide the expected address, and returned success or failure, to avoid potential social engineering: if the user is simply told the signing address, someone could use vanitygen to create a similar-looking address and attempt to fool the verifier when they compare it. The recently merged Verify Message dialog introduces this attack vector.\n\nI propose making the Address field editable, and having the Verify button simply display \"Signature valid\" or invalid in a messagebox.",
